<exploration xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="PA-changing-linear-3-ex">

	<statement>

		<p>
			<ol marker="a.">
				<li>
					<p>
						Let <m>y = f(x) = 7 - 3x</m>.  Determine <m>AV_{[-3,-1]}</m>, <m>AV_{[2,5]}</m>, and <m>AV_{[4,10]}</m> for the function <m>f</m>.
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>
						Let <m>y = g(x)</m> be given by the data in <xref ref="T-PA-changing-linear-3-ex-2">Table</xref>.
					</p>

					<table xml:id="T-PA-changing-linear-3-ex-2">
						<title>A table that defines the function <m>y = g(x)</m>.</title>
							<tabular>
								<row bottom="minor" halign="center">
									<cell><m>x</m></cell>
									<cell><m>-5</m></cell>
									<cell><m>-4</m></cell>
									<cell><m>-3</m></cell>
									<cell><m>-2</m></cell>
									<cell><m>-1</m></cell>
									<cell><m>0</m></cell>																		
									<cell><m>1</m></cell>
									<cell><m>2</m></cell>
									<cell><m>3</m></cell>
									<cell><m>4</m></cell>
									<cell><m>5</m></cell>
								</row>
								<row halign="center">
									<cell><m>g(x)</m></cell>
									<cell><m>-2.75</m></cell>
									<cell><m>-2.25</m></cell>
									<cell><m>-1.75</m></cell>
									<cell><m>-1.25</m></cell>
									<cell><m>-0.75</m></cell>
									<cell><m>-0.25</m></cell>																	
									<cell><m>0.25</m></cell>
									<cell><m>0.75</m></cell>
									<cell><m>1.25</m></cell>
									<cell><m>1.75</m></cell>
									<cell><m>2.25</m></cell>
								</row>
							</tabular>
					</table>

					<p>
						Determine <m>AV_{[-5,-2]}</m>, <m>AV_{[-1,1]}</m>, and <m>AV_{[0,4]}</m> for the function <m>g</m>.
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>
						Consider the function <m>y = h(x)</m> defined by the graph in <xref ref="F-PA-changing-linear-3-ex-3">Figure</xref>.
					</p>

					<figure xml:id="F-PA-changing-linear-3-ex-3">
						<caption>The graph of <m>y = h(x)</m>.</caption>
						<image width="45%" source="images/linear-PA-ex-3" />
					</figure>

					<p>
						Determine <m>AV_{[-5,-2]}</m>, <m>AV_{[-1,1]}</m>, and <m>AV_{[0,4]}</m> for the function <m>h</m>.
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>
						What do all three examples above have in common?  How do they differ?
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>
						For the function <m>y = f(x) = 7 - 3x</m> from (a), find the simplest expression you can for 
						<me>
							AV_{[a,b]} = \frac{f(b)-f(a)}{b-a}
						</me>
						where <m>a \ne b</m>.
					</p>
				</li>
			</ol>
		</p>
	</statement>

</exploration>
